duck: A constellation in the Northern Hemisphere near Cassiopeia and Draco.

wiki.text:
'Cepheus' (Ancient Greek: 'Κηφεύς', Kepheús) may refer to:

In 'Greek Mythology':
* Cepheus, King of Aethiopia, in Greek mythology
* Cepheus, King of Tegea, the king of Tegea, Arcadia in Greek mythology

In 'Astronomy':
* Cepheus (constellation), one of the 88 modern constellations
* Cepheus (crater), a lunar impact crater

In 'Modern Fiction':
* Cepheus Daidalos, a fictional character in the manga and anime, Saint Seiya
* In the ''Soul'' series video games, both the character Cepheus, and a weapon,
  the Cepheus Seal
* Cepheus, the FM king in Mega Man Star Force
* In the Galaxy Railways, one of the squads is named the Cepheus Platoon.

'Other' uses:
* USS Cepheus (AKA-18), an Andromeda class attack cargo ship
* CEPHEUS, the 'C'ost 'E'fficient 'P'assive 'H'ouses as 'Eu'ropean 'S'tandards
  research project
